Program: Omnibus
Title: Refugees - a Burden or a Bonus?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m0r
Last Broadcast Date: 06 July 2000
From Huguenots to Ugandan Asians, providing refuge to those fleeing from persecution is a 300 year British tradition. A look at how various waves of refugees have been treated and how they have adapted to,and changed, British culture and society.